<subSubSection id="C68B287FD7BE644A0BCF0FEF8B1ABD00" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D1757018E0BC3EC4578AABA01EE61642" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="998429B1A1EDD23EB77EF33CFB969120" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Antennae yellowish brown with scape yellow. Midlobe of mesoscutum with two pairs of long setae. Legs mostly yellowish white with fore and hind coxae white, mid coxae yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="03AB33E3F2BFA60E1A19B7229A98DC7C" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="description">
<paragraph id="020A73CDAE7CDD64A68CAA1408F13826" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A5BCB38561E765ACDD69EF09BE15EDC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="6F35C539DFAB004F8FA389001B952566" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 1.8 mm, fore wing length 1.5 mm. Body yellow. Antennae yellowish brown with scape yellow. Legs mostly yellowish white except fore and hind coxae white, mid coxae yellow. Gaster dorsally mostly yellow with a brown patch and lateral margins brown, ventrally mostly whitish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="115B7712BEB4A27CA253A0A677CB517C" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="61F88D3B55AF90EF3FD890C3EA03CC15" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Head</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="D0007A119392C263953C98CEBF556548" captionStart="Figures 11–16" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 11 - 16. D. hainana sp. nov., female, holotype 11 habitus in lateral view 12 gaster in dorsal view 13 head in frontal view 14 fore wing 15 habitus in dorsal view 16 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671713" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="882383A468949C2D4B707072D32F14EB" captionStart="Figures 11–16" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 11 - 16. D. hainana sp. nov., female, holotype 11 habitus in lateral view 12 gaster in dorsal view 13 head in frontal view 14 fore wing 15 habitus in dorsal view 16 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671713" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">13</figureCitation>
) 1.4
<normalizedToken id="53B3E85B6EC529A0A80A02C9B009FF93" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as high in frontal view and 2.4
<normalizedToken id="96CA7362929F88D3B9E6ECD3244FCE4C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long in dorsal view. Frons weakly sculptured. Vertex with engraved reticulation, meshes isodiametric. POL 2.4
<normalizedToken id="C41FCD4FEFACDEC7F4C9A774381E91F3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
OOL. Malar space 0.3
<normalizedToken id="B24BB6ECFD4A2376E9A21A35A87C5124" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye height. Occiput weakly reticulate. Relative measurements (length: width): scape = 29: 5; pedicel = 11: 5; F1 = 13: 5; F2 = 10: 5; F3 = 10: 6; F4 = 9: 6; clava = 15: 5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="35AFF152E1E00B4576CA354597B56DA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="475705D24833AD21B9ACFD58BCF4462A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B0B75CFAFBA39427427CD1CFF66366FF" captionStart="Figures 11–16" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 11 - 16. D. hainana sp. nov., female, holotype 11 habitus in lateral view 12 gaster in dorsal view 13 head in frontal view 14 fore wing 15 habitus in dorsal view 16 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671713" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">15</figureCitation>
). Notauli straight, ending laterad to inner angle of axilla. Midlobe of mesoscutum punctate with two pairs of long setae, lateral lobe of mesoscutum reticulate. Axillae weakly reticulate and separated from each other. Scutellum longer than mesoscutum with two pairs of long setae, sublateral grooves meet posteriorly. Spiracle with a transverse carina anteriorly, slightly separated from metanotum by a distance shorter than a diameter of spiracle; each propodeal callus with seven or eight setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79200CFAB5A19C1BAC4C5894C4D6F02D" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="2A3390513A301CB13FCE7A8EE6FB59A3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="3B36A193B4345DAEE1C1D35EB00B907A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Wings</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Fore wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ED9F2155DCC18E740DA86665B3DEC91C" captionStart="Figures 11–16" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 11 - 16. D. hainana sp. nov., female, holotype 11 habitus in lateral view 12 gaster in dorsal view 13 head in frontal view 14 fore wing 15 habitus in dorsal view 16 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671713" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">14</figureCitation>
) 2.3
<normalizedToken id="B5699139BE9B927362A0BE980FE7035D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. Speculum narrow. Relative measurements (length): SMV = 35; MV= 36; PMV= 16; STV= 12. Hind wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3B994A143B1B85B0D3FF078BEE53BD71" captionStart="Figures 11–16" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 11 - 16. D. hainana sp. nov., female, holotype 11 habitus in lateral view 12 gaster in dorsal view 13 head in frontal view 14 fore wing 15 habitus in dorsal view 16 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671713" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">16</figureCitation>
) ~ 4.0
<normalizedToken id="8C231FAECC7A5DE0B89793C10D7C723B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD34218E1BD521A22ABFA53F5AC0697F" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="3E2FC663BDE6F46DC867E6265547FE6F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Metasoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8F887110CEA108F55E1E3C251CE73A48" captionStart="Figures 11–16" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 11 - 16. D. hainana sp. nov., female, holotype 11 habitus in lateral view 12 gaster in dorsal view 13 head in frontal view 14 fore wing 15 habitus in dorsal view 16 hind wing. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80671.figures11-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671713" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">12</figureCitation>
). Gaster ovate; 1.8
<normalizedToken id="90B9E62CB78BC2216EF33EE6CEFA7594" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide and 1.3
<normalizedToken id="23B412212300C482661267C995530D54" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as mesosoma. Ovipositor exserted beyond apex of gaster.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40418244C716E54F0B87C5A60F814756" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="BCE0CC046CD352920FBC257BD23386DF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1B241649B9FFBCB7DA82C8C35678713" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="host">
<paragraph id="8338DF8D5A45CEB7BA5CA3B967CE5879" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Host.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADBCFA4C85303CC17249E1AF28D6F029" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="069FA8B46E8FB8594B136546ED9E65C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="799FDBFE9D0D1741DE4C4612609D566D" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A29813EF22652DC9F3C80A2EB876D57F" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">China (Hainan).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3280F5701B79CA186466956CBE9C1A64" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E4A54123CBA831F78870737E02C28B07" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B767C9186D8768B596F1B3ACA450D8E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">The specific name is derived from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="81F90DFB4340CE2EE5B0EA3A4F34A656" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="EEE31D4CA9351AFA8B9DB09785E890F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="594C2390EDB4594781E42AE416798CE8" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="D1D3046D5F8929458983A29A88F11042" authorityName="Fan &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diglyphomorphomyia hainana" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana">
<emphasis id="094FE67778C83D060204AE80A4DB34CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Diglyphomorphomyia hainana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="7B86EF9AFFF566EFDDB0D04D65E1EE9B" class="Insecta" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. aequus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequus">
<emphasis id="E77CE9D231118C91F7DF58F29F2205F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">D. aequus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zhu &amp; Huang, 2003 in sharing a body that is mostly yellow, and a gaster bearing a brown patch, but can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="471C690023D317BCE58C4DCC5131A596" class="Insecta" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. aequus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequus">
<emphasis id="8B778F32A77E82217C743899F3FD2900" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">D. aequus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: antennae yellowish brown with scape yellow (antenna brown with scape, pedicel, and F1 yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="8A095FE982964C1442315747A9BC4211" class="Insecta" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. aequus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequus">
<emphasis id="D0AAFC49B557BED7E5E8353B54AD142D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">D. aequus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); POL 2.4
<normalizedToken id="7C5577CEB8D642244E334DB24FC3AB14" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
OOL (POL 2.8
<normalizedToken id="C8FCADC8A0AB77F16756E6A4359A74BC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
OOL in 
<taxonomicName id="5EF322FFFE708862E46153DB8BBB465B" class="Insecta" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. aequus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequus">
<emphasis id="7DE3D8CD3661DB13FC389CC7104C3CB1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">D. aequus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); legs mostly yellowish white with fore and hind coxae white, mid coxae yellow (legs yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="E66B3EE9C7DE163C576AC3D15B78A3FC" class="Insecta" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. aequus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequus">
<emphasis id="77DB9BD1D431A45D91DBAC5102430958" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">D. aequus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
